cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a stochastic derivative-free algorithm for numerical optimization, which is often used in evolutionary computing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of optimization algorithms in black-box scenarios, which is a common problem in machine learning.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the time and memory complexity of the LM-CMA algorithm.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an alternative optimization algorithm that can be used in AI applications.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the performance of the LM-CMA algorithm on non-linear, non-convex optimization problems, which are common in control systems.
